title: Sample Book (India), 18th century
medium:

markings:
Watermark of London 1787: Fleur de lys in a shield surmounted by  crown.

inscribed:
First page has two ink signatures "John Philips."
Daily schedule (?) on blank page near back of book.
description: Ninety-eight textile samples mounted on hand-made paper and bound in gold-tooled red leather. 53 silk samples; 28 silk-and-cotton samples; 16 cotton; and 1 linen.
